  "text": "There was very little evidence that the time of birth (birth cohort) was associated with change in diet quality. Study participants aged $55 y in 2007 had greater increases in diet quality than those in that age group 15 y previously (of borderline significance in the subgroup aged 55-64 y; P = 0.06), which agrees with the findings from a Swedish study [CITATION_1] that showed an improvement in diet quality in later-born cohorts.",
